def column_values(df):

    #     
    string_columns = df.select_dtypes(exclude=['number']).columns

    #      
    for column in string_columns:
        df[column] = df[column].apply(lambda x: x.lower().replace(' ', '_'))

    return df

def check_data(data, bins=10, figsize=(15, 10)):
    print('  :')
    display(data.head())

    print('\n  :')
    display(data.tail())

    print('\n :')
    display(data.shape)

    print('\n     :')
    display(data.info())

    #  
    print('\n (  ):')
    total_missing = data.isnull().sum().sort_values(ascending=False)
    percent_missing = (data.isnull().sum() / data.shape[0]).sort_values(ascending=False)
    missing_data = pd.concat([total_missing, percent_missing], axis=1, keys=['total', 'percent'])

    # ,   
    if missing_data['total'].sum() > 0:
        print(missing_data[missing_data['total'] > 0])  #     
    else:
        print('   .')

    #   
    numeric_columns = data.select_dtypes(include=['number']).columns
    numeric_columns = numeric_columns[numeric_columns != 'id']  #   'id'
    
    #     
    discrete_columns = []
    continuous_columns = []
    for col in numeric_columns:
        if data[col].nunique() < 24:  #     
            discrete_columns.append(col)
        else:
            continuous_columns.append(col)
    
    #     
    if continuous_columns:  #     
        print('\n      ():')
        #       
        n_cols = 2
        n_rows = (len(continuous_columns) + n_cols - 1) // n_cols
        
        fig, axes = plt.subplots(n_rows, n_cols, figsize=figsize)
        axes = axes.flatten()
        
        for i, col in enumerate(continuous_columns):
            axes[i].hist(data[col], bins=bins, color='blue')
            axes[i].grid(True)
            axes[i].set_title(f'  {col}')
            axes[i].set_xlabel(col)
            axes[i].set_ylabel('')
        
        #   ,   
        for j in range(i + 1, len(axes)):
            fig.delaxes(axes[j])
        
        plt.tight_layout() #   
        plt.show()
    
    #      
    if discrete_columns:  #     
        print('\n      ( ):')
        #       
        n_cols = 2
        n_rows = (len(discrete_columns) + n_cols - 1) // n_cols
        
        fig, axes = plt.subplots(n_rows, n_cols, figsize=figsize)
        axes = axes.flatten()  #   
        
        for i, col in enumerate(discrete_columns):
            value_counts = data[col].value_counts().sort_index()
            axes[i].bar(value_counts.index, value_counts.values, color='green')
            axes[i].grid(True)            
            axes[i].set_title(f'  {col}')
            axes[i].set_xlabel(col)
            axes[i].set_ylabel('')
        
        #   ,   
        for j in range(i + 1, len(axes)):
            fig.delaxes(axes[j])
        
        plt.tight_layout() #   
        plt.show()

    #   
    categorical_columns = data.select_dtypes(exclude=['number']).columns
    if not categorical_columns.empty:
        print('\n    :')
        for col in categorical_columns:
            print(f'\n: {col}')
            print(data[col].value_counts())
            print(f'  : {data[col].nunique()}')
            
    #   
    duplicate_rows = data.duplicated().sum()
    
    if duplicate_rows > 0:
        print(f"\n {duplicate_rows}   .")
        print(":")
        display(data[data.duplicated()])
    else:
        print("\n   .")

def number_columns(data, column, bins=50):
    
    #  
    description = data[column].describe()
    print(f"\n===    '{column}' ===")
    print(description)
    
    #      IQR
    Q1 = data[column].quantile(0.25)
    Q3 = data[column].quantile(0.75)
    IQR = Q3 - Q1
    lower_bound = Q1 - 1.5 * IQR
    upper_bound = Q3 + 1.5 * IQR
    
    outliers = data[(data[column] < lower_bound) | (data[column] > upper_bound)]
    print(f"\n   '{column}': {len(outliers)}")
    
    #    boxplot
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(15, 6))
    
    sns.histplot(x=data[column], kde=True, ax=ax[0], bins=bins, color='skyblue')
    ax[0].set_title(f'  {column}')
    ax[0].set_xlabel(column)
    ax[0].set_ylabel('')
    
    sns.boxplot(x=data[column], ax=ax[1], color='lightgreen')
    ax[1].set_title(f'Boxplot  {column}')
    ax[1].set_xlabel(column)
    
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

def discrete_columns(data, column):
    #  
    description = data[column].describe()
    print(f"\n===    '{column}' ===")
    print(description)
    
    #      IQR
    Q1 = data[column].quantile(0.25)
    Q3 = data[column].quantile(0.75)
    IQR = Q3 - Q1
    lower_bound = Q1 - 1.5 * IQR
    upper_bound = Q3 + 1.5 * IQR
    
    outliers = data[(data[column] < lower_bound) | (data[column] > upper_bound)]
    print(f"\n   '{column}': {len(outliers)}")
    
    #     
    fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(15, 6))
    
    #  
    value_counts = data[column].value_counts().sort_index()
    sns.barplot(x=value_counts.index, y=value_counts.values, color='skyblue', ax=axes[0])
    axes[0].set_title(f'   {column}')
    axes[0].set_xlabel(column)
    axes[0].set_ylabel('')
    
    for i in range(len(value_counts)):
        axes[0].text(i, value_counts.values[i], value_counts.values[i], ha='center', va='bottom')
    
    # Boxplot
    sns.boxplot(x=data[column], color='lightgreen', ax=axes[1])
    axes[1].set_title(f'Boxplot  {column}')
    axes[1].set_xlabel(column)
    
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

def display_outliers(data, column):

    #      IQR
    Q1 = data[column].quantile(0.25)
    Q3 = data[column].quantile(0.75)
    IQR = Q3 - Q1
    lower_bound = Q1 - 1.5 * IQR
    upper_bound = Q3 + 1.5 * IQR

    #    
    outliers = data[(data[column] < lower_bound) | (data[column] > upper_bound)]
    if not outliers.empty:
        print(f"   '{column}':")
        display(outliers)
    else:
        print(f"     '{column}'.")
        
    return outliers

def plot_categorical_columns(df):
    #   
    categorical_columns = df.select_dtypes(include=['object', 'category']).columns.tolist()
    
    #  
    num_plots = len(categorical_columns)
    rows = (num_plots + 2) // 3
    fig, axs = plt.subplots(rows, 3, figsize=(18, 5 * rows))
    axs = axs.flatten()
    
    #   
    for i, column in enumerate(categorical_columns):
        #   
        value_counts = df[column].value_counts()
        
        #   
        total = value_counts.sum()  #     
        axs[i].pie(
            value_counts, 
            labels=value_counts.index, 
            autopct=lambda pct: f'{pct:.1f}% ({int(pct/100.*total)})',  #    
            startangle=90
        )
        axs[i].set_title(column)  #   
    
    #   ,   ,  
    for j in range(i + 1, len(axs)):
        fig.delaxes(axs[j])
    
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

#   OHE-
ohe_pipe = Pipeline(
    [
        (
            'simpleImputer_ohe', 
            SimpleImputer(missing_values=np.nan, strategy='most_frequent')
        ),
        (
            'ohe', 
            OneHotEncoder(drop='first', handle_unknown='ignore', sparse_output=False)
        )
    ]
)
In[70]:
#   Ordinal-
ord_pipe = Pipeline(
    [
        (
            'simpleImputer_before_ord', 
            SimpleImputer(missing_values=np.nan, strategy='most_frequent')
        ),
        (
            'ord',
            OrdinalEncoder(
                categories=[
                    ['', ''],
                ], 
                handle_unknown='use_encoded_value',
                unknown_value=np.nan
            )
        ),
        (
            'simpleImputer_after_ord', 
            SimpleImputer(missing_values=np.nan, strategy='most_frequent')
        )
    ]
)
